ect understanding of this liaison helps the reader to clarify many enigmatic images in Russian literary works of the last two centuries and to understand the roots of a particular cultural falsification that played an important role in the anti-Semitic mythology of the twentieth century.  afunded by National Endowment for the Humanities and The Andrew W. Mellon Foundation Humanities Open Book Program  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCabala in literature. 0aCabalaxHistory. 0aCabalaxInfluence. 0aOccultismzRussiaxHistory. 0aRussian literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aRussian literaturexThemes, motives. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Russian & Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh2 aNational Endowment for the Humanities and The Andrew W. Mellon Foundation Humanities Open Book Programefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Backlist eBook-Package 2008-2013z978311102408008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Backlist eBook-Package 2008-2015z978311068814608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertReligious Studies ASPz978311071683240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781618116918?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781618116918zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781618116918/original  a978-3-11-068814-6 Academic Studies Press Backlist eBook-Package 2008-2015c2008d2015  a978-3-11-071683-2 Religious Studies ASP  a978-3-11-102408-0 Academic Studies Press Backlist eBook-Package 2008-2013c2008d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA